{"session_id":"svc-1778832463811793203","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-15T08:07:44.707439298Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"codex","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"gpt-5.4","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-edd8085b-20260515T080727-8519b696","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-edd8085b\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ehousekeeping: reap orphan ddx worktrees and stale worker/execution state: part 3\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Parent bead ddx-c191e91a is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 3 of 3 of that parent scope.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;PROBLEM\u0026#xA;DDx-managed filesystem state accumulates indefinitely. On the Fizeau project (sibling repo, /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau) on 2026-05-14:\u0026#xA;- /var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/ contained 9,735 inodes across ~9700+ directories. Many were .execute-bead-wt-* worktrees dating back to 2026-05-07 (a week stale). Each is a full repo checkout, multiplying repo size on disk.\u0026#xA;- .ddx/workers/ held 35 agent-loop-\u0026lt;nano-id\u0026gt;/ directories. Most show last_activity_at older than 1 hour with no live process. They keep persisting per-attempt status.json entries.\u0026#xA;- .ddx/executions/ held 44 attempt directories. Some have unmerged result.json state (a previous merge or worker crash left them in DU). No automatic GC.\u0026#xA;- .ddx/attachments/ holds 355 per-bead artifact directories. They flood `git status` as untracked since nothing gitignores them.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- `ddx try` creates a worktree under `/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-\u0026lt;bead\u0026gt;-\u0026lt;timestamp\u0026gt;-\u0026lt;hash\u0026gt;/` and only sometimes cleans up. Failure paths (worktree_lost, execution_failed, process crash) consistently leave the worktree behind. There\u0026#39;s no startup reaper for stale worktrees.\u0026#xA;- `ddx work` and `ddx try` write a worker status.json under .ddx/workers/agent-loop-\u0026lt;nano-id\u0026gt;/ and the writer is responsible for cleanup. Process crashes leave the directory behind; no startup reaper claims them.\u0026#xA;- .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;timestamp\u0026gt;/ is meant to be retained as evidence (per CONTRACT-003 / FEAT-010 evidence pile). But there\u0026#39;s no retention policy: directories accumulate forever. Some land in unmerged git state after partial commits.\u0026#xA;- .ddx/attachments/ and .ddx/run-state*.json are written by every ddx invocation, but the project\u0026#39;s .gitignore policy for them is inconsistent (.ddx/executions is ignored; .ddx/attachments and .ddx/run-state.json appear in `git status` constantly).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;1. Add a startup reaper to `ddx work` and `ddx try`: on launch, scan /var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/, identify worktrees whose parent ddx-try/ddx-work process is dead (no PID match), `git worktree remove` + `rm -rf` them. Bound the scan to N=200 per launch so a cold start doesn\u0026#39;t take forever. Configurable via DDX_WORKTREE_REAP_MAX_AGE (default 72h).\u0026#xA;2. Add a startup reaper for `.ddx/workers/agent-loop-*/`: read status.json\u0026#39;s `pid` and `last_activity_at`; if pid is gone OR activity \u0026gt; 30 min stale, remove the directory.\u0026#xA;3. Add a configurable execution-evidence retention policy:\u0026#xA;...[truncated]\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Implement only this child acceptance slice:\u0026#xA;- `ddx init` (or the equivalent template-update path) writes .gitignore entries for `.ddx/attachments/`, `.ddx/run-state.json`, `.ddx/run-state/`, `.ddx/workers/`.\u0026#xA;- cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;- CHANGELOG.md notes the reaper + retention behavior + env knobs.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `ddx init` (or the equivalent template-update path) writes .gitignore entries for `.ddx/attachments/`, `.ddx/run-state.json`, `.ddx/run-state/`, `.ddx/workers/`.\u0026#xA;2. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;3. CHANGELOG.md notes the reaper + retention behavior + env knobs.\u0026#xA;4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:agent, area:execution, kind:cleanup, decomposed\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-c191e91a\" base-rev=\"4467ed894037f721ee372432d80a389ac16ff641\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260515T080727-8519b696","base_rev":"4467ed894037f721ee372432d80a389ac16ff641","bead_id":"ddx-edd8085b","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696","correlation_id":"ddx-edd8085b:20260515T080727-8519b696","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260515T080727-8519b696/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"a1a13b2d9a73e81b4796f51b409a38914487a738d3c70d63cc67d8f49d3c0800","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-08aceca0","worker_id":""}}}
